      "Icon": "⛪",
      "Description": "Today we traveled, by train, to the Sudanese Refugee encampment called Malakasa near Sfendali, Greece. It was about a 1 hour trip. This encampment is primarily male refugees looking for temporary or permenate EU passports (their papers). They live in shipping containers and have very little. We played Soccer (futbol) with them for 5 hours. They all have different financial means, which means some have shoes and some do not. So, everyone who played, had to play in only socks to level the playing field. It was a great day. In the morning we climbed the hill and stairs of the Acropolis to see the Parthenon and other Greek ruins."
    },
